dogū}}\'\'—a "spaceman" clay figurine from the {{wp|Jōmon period}} of Japanese history. It also seems to resemble {{wp|Hopi Kachina figure}}s.\n\n====Name origin====\nBaltoy may be a combination of \'\'balance\'\' and \'\'toy\'\'.\n\nYajilon is an abbreviation of 弥次郎兵衛 \'\'yajirobe\'e\'\' (balancing toy).\n\n==In other languages==\n{{Other languages|type=Ground|type2=Psychic\n|ja=ヤジロン \'\'Yajilon\'\'|jameaning=Abbreviation of {{tt|弥次郎兵衛 \'\'yajirobe\'e\'\'|balancing toy}}.\n|fr=Balbuto|frmeaning=From {{tt|\'\'Balbutier\'\'|to be in its infancy}} and \'\'{{wp|Weeble|Culbuto}}\'\'\n|es=Baltoy|esmeaning=Same as English name\n|de=Puppance|demeaning=From \'\'{{tt|Puppe|doll}}\'\' and \'\'Balance\'\'\n|it=Baltoy|itmeaning=Same as English name\n|ko=오뚝군 \'\'Ohttukgun\'\'|komeaning=From {{tt|오뚜기 \'\'ottuki\'\'|roly-poly toy}} and likely {{tt|군(君) \'\'gun\'\'|young man}}\n|zh_cmn=天秤偶 \'\'Tiānpíng\'ǒu\'\'|zh_cmnmeaning=Literally "{{wp|Libra (constellation)|Libra}} figurine"\n}}\n<br clear="left">\n\n==External links==\n\n{{-}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Ground|type2=Psychic}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Ground|prevnum=342|prev=Crawdaunt|nextnum=344|next=Claydol}}\n|}\n{{Project Pokédex notice}}\n\n[[Category:Shadow Pokémon in Pokémon XD]]\n[[Category:Artificial Pokémon]]\n\n[[de:Puppance]]\n[[es:Baltoy]]\n[[fr:Balbuto]]\n[[it:Baltoy]]\n[[ja:ヤジロン]]\n[[zh:天秤偶]]'}